HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton karuwar sabbin kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14%
Kasar Sin ta samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sabbin mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da kuma AIDS.
Fiye da mutane 820,000 a kasar sun kamu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya.
An samu sabbin mutane 40,000 a kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka ana watsa su ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda canji ne daga yanayin da ya gabata.
A dā, cutar HIV ta yaɗu da sauri a wasu ɓangarorin ƙasar Sin ta wurin jini da aka yi wa jini da ke ɗauke da cutar.
Amma, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taron da aka gudanar a lardin Yunnan.
Amma duk da haka, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000 a kowace shekara.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i na zama babbar matsala a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An daina la'akari da luwadi a matsayin haramtacce a kasar Sin tun 1997, amma an ce nuna bambanci ga LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Bincike ya nuna cewa saboda ra'ayoyin masu ra'ayin mazan jiya a kasar, kashi 70-90% na mazajen da suke yin jima'i da maza suna yin aure da mata.
